abstract: Greece and European Union struggle to put in place structures needed to enforce agreement that requires Turkey to stem flow of migrants leaving its shores and Greece to send back those not eligible for asylum; hundreds of refugees arrive in Greece on first day of new policy and processing centers are overwhelmed.
lead_paragraph: After a European Union deal with Turkey took effect, migrants by the hundreds continued to reach the Greek islands, where processing centers were not yet adequately staffed.

headline.main: Greece Struggles to Enforce Migrant Accord on First Day
